This paper presents a multi-robot system equipped with a range-based relative positioning system, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of onboard sensing and fusion of sensor data, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). The system is designed to perform cooperative tasks, which is a topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of simulations and experiments, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) for data processing and analysis.
